The proof strategy is to assume that the coloring is good (i.e., there exists a monochromatic triple) and derive a contradiction. The `interval_cases` tactic will generate cases for all possible values of $i$ and $j$ in the range 1 to 8. For each case, we need to show that the assumption leads to a contradiction.

